103. Create a very simple pageview counter by using ‘isset’ to check if the pageview variable has
already been created.
code:
<?php
// Start the session to store pageview count
session_start();

// Check if 'pageview' session variable exists
if(isset($_SESSION['pageview'])) {
    $_SESSION['pageview']++;  // Increment pageview
} else {
    $_SESSION['pageview'] = 1; // Initialize pageview
}

?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple Pageview Counter</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Pageview Counter Example</h2>

<p>You have visited this page <strong><?php echo $_SESSION['pageview']; ?></strong> times.</p>

</body>
</html>
